<br>
Second attempt, I summoned mod rods for every caster beforehand and I just nuked stright up without using banishment.  Personally I think we nuked a little too hard and mobs were falling faster than needed.  I was in a dilemma though because if I didn't nuke at a certian rate, the wizard would pick up the difference and use up his mana too fast.  <br>
<br>
By the boss mob I was oom, but the cleric was at 80mana.  The wizard was oom as well.  I used boots of bladecalling about 4 times I think, and I regenned enough mana to do about 3k worth of nukes as well.  The wizard medded most of the fight and hit it at the end with nukes.    We had several close calls with the rogues tanking, but everyone survived at the end.  Everyone ended up clicking their mod rods twice.  <br>
<br>
Having another mage instead of a wizard in the group definately would have been much better.  1 FoT per mob is all the nuking that is needed.  2 mages would easily be able to manage better than 1 FoT per mob, plus the extra pet damage would have added damage. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kopla>Kopla</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#333333>(11/5/02 11:29:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> These trials are a pain.  They take people who know there class and good DPS.  Many say any combination can do it... that is not the case unless all are level 65.  Everyone should be level 61, anyone below that you will have to have a hi DPS class to make up for.  The executioner trial has been the easiest that i have seen so far.<br>
<br>
About banishment.  You are a fool if you don't use it.  It saves everyone's mana, just malosini first.  With malosini I have had 1 out of 23 resist banish.  <br>
<br>
If you really want to shoot the random lower DPS people through the trials get 2 mages in the group.  Have your main tank ignore any rocks that spawn besides the named one.  <br>
<br>
If you want to win don't go pick up group.  IF you win with a pick up group consider yourself extremely lucky to have fallen in with the people who know how to do their jobs, there are so few out there.  I like these trials because you have to have skill, you have to know your job and the people you are working with.<br>
<br>
Good luck, and don't help the lemons through, they don't deserve it.<br>
