<br>
If your group sucks so much they need banish, that's just sad.<br>
<br>
Banish = 500 mana evocation based.<br>
<br>
SOFB = 334 mana conj based.<br>
<br>
Banish is only for if you F up aggro or something, and wait til the last wave, otherwise your group may turn out to just F up every wave... and banishment has recast time.<br>
<br>
So if you're group can't do with 1 SOFB instead of banish, then your group can't do the trials. <p>Insert HTML babble here.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=zaniel>Zaniel</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 124<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 1:35:14 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=29>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> Did the trials with myself, a necro, a cleric, 2 warriors and rogue and we stomped it. No slow or CC, the warriors just used their slow hammers on the Executioner.<br>
