<br>
1.  Banishment is a quick way to reset the Executioner if things go bad.<br>
2.  Rock mobs (the summoned ones) cannot be mez'd.<br>
3.  It's easier for a tank or enchanter to deal with the aggro of three mobs rather than four.<br>
4.  If there are multiple Rock (summoned) mobs, banishing one at the beginning of the round means that Banishment will likely have recycled by the next round.  For that round your Cleric only has to repair the damage of three mobs, not 4, saving mana. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style=""><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365">Kathodos</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Battle Cleric of Tunare - Tholuxe Paells</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style=""><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=59365">Kantreach</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Arch Mage Antagonist - Tholuxe Paells</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krilenspiritlink>Krilen Spiritlink</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 502<br> <font color=#333333>(11/7/02 6:51:00 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=399.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Banishment</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;60 Epic Mage (me), 60 Paladin, 59 Warrior, 59 Druid, 59 Epic Cleric, and 56 Chanter. &quot;<br>
